We have previously used the difference between two squares factorisation a^2 - b^2 = (a + b)(a - b) extensively.

However, without i = sqrt(-1) we have been unable to factorise the sum of two squares.

Notice that a^2 + b^2 = a^2 - b^2*i^2 {as i^2 = -1}
= (a + bi)(a - bi) {the difference between two squares}
